#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:1
msgid "Inverse Properties"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:3
msgid ""
"The [Inverse Properties "
"module](https://omeka.org/s/modules/InverseProperties/) allows "
"administrators to define inverse properties between resources (items, "
"item sets, and media) so that property values can be concretely linked in"
" both directions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:5
msgid ""
"To install Inverse Properties, follow the instructions for [Installing "
"Modules](https://omeka.org/s/docs/user-manual/modules/#installing-"
"modules) on the Modules documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:7
msgid "Assigning Inverse Properties in Resource Templates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:9
msgid ""
"To use Inverse Properties, you must already have at least one resource "
"template that has properties using the default or resource data types. "
"Once the module is installed, it should appear in the left-hand "
"navigation. When you select Inverse Properties, you will be taken to a "
"table of available resource templates. In addition to label and owner, "
"there is a column indicating each template's inverse property count. To "
"add inverse properties to a resource template, click edit (pencil icon)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:11
msgid ""
"![Edit existing resource template to add inverse "
"properties.](modulesfiles/inverseProperties_edit.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:11
msgid "Edit existing resource template to add inverse properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:13
msgid ""
"To assign an inverse property, select an inverse for that property from "
"the dropdown menu. You can either scroll through the list of options or "
"use the search bar to jump to a specific property. You can select a "
"property from any vocabulary. A property cannot be the inverse of itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:15
msgid ""
"![Select inverse property from dropdown "
"menu.](modulesfiles/inverseProperties_dropdown.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:15
msgid "Select inverse property from dropdown menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:17
msgid ""
"Once you have selected all the inverse properties for that resource "
"template, click \"Submit\" in the upper right corner to save your "
"changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:19
msgid "Inverse Properties In Action"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:21
msgid ""
"When adding or editing an item, select a resource template that has "
"inverse properties. Then, in a property that has an inverse property,  "
"click \"Omeka resource\". Then, click \"Item\" and select the item you "
"wish to add from the drawer. After selecting the item, be sure to click "
"\"Select resource\" at the bottom of the drawer to add the item to the "
"metadata field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:23
msgid "![Add inverse property to item.](modulesfiles/inverseProperties_add.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:23
msgid "Add inverse property to item."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/modules/inverseproperties.md:25
msgid ""
"Once you have finished editing the item, click \"Save\". The item you "
"added as a linked resource should now appear on the item's show page."
msgstr ""

